<TEXT>
the lead prosecutor in new yorks pizza 
connection heroin trial was named friday to coordinate the 
investigation in the bombing deaths of a federal judge and a black 
savannah lawyer 
louis freeh an assistant us attorney in new york was named 
to head the justice department investigation and prosecution of the 
case 
attorney general dick thornburgh said he picked an outside 
prosecutor to oversee the probe because the mail bombs case spanned 
several jurisdictions 
freeh handled the 17month new york trial of an mafia ring that 
distributed tons of heroin and cocaine in the united states he won 
prosecutions against 18 members of the 16 billion ring that used 
pizzerias as fronts to distribute large amounts of heroin and 
cocaine from 1975 to 1984 
the reputed former chief of the sicilian mafia gaetano 
badalamenti and his associate salvatore catalano received 
45year prison terms for running the ring 
in the present case four packages containing explosives were 
sent to sites in alabama florida and georgia over a fourday 
period in middecember two of them exploded killing 11th us 
circuit court judge robert s vance at his home near birmingham 
ala and savannah alderman robert robinson at his law office 
packages containing explosives were removed from the 11th 
circuits headquarters building in atlanta and the jacksonville 
fla office of the national association for the advancement of 
colored people 
hundreds of law enforcement personnel have been working on 
this investigation and cooperation among the various districts has 
been excellent thornburgh said 
as this multidistrict investigation has progressed however 
it has become evident that the naming of the a single coordinating 
prosecutor with overall responsibility is essential the attorney 
general said 
