<TEXT>
the army on friday ordered the 
arrest of brazils former secret service chief after he criticized 
president fernando collor de mello and the new governments 
economic reform plans officials said 
also disciplined for similar criticism was retired gen euclydes 
figueiredo the brother of former military president joao 
figueiredo 
carlos tinoco the minister of the army announced the 
punishments in a televised interview 
the presidential palace refused to comment 
both generals were punished under a military code that prohibits 
military personnel from making political statements or attacks on 
the president to the press without authorization from an armed 
forces minister 
the confrontation underlies growing tensions between collor and 
conservative elements of brazils armed forces 
tinoco said gen newton cruz the former head of the recently 
abolished secret service was ordered arrested for 10 days in an 
army barracks in brasilia after attacking collor in an interview 
published friday in the o estado de sao paulo newspaper 
cruz criticized collor for firing 400000 public employees 
earlier this week to speed his antiinflation program 
i think we live in a dictatorship validated by the judiciary 
and the congress cruz was quoted as saying if former 
president jose sarney erred by lacking authority and determination 
collor fails for his excessive aggressiveness 
tinoco said cruz confirmed basically all of his criticisms 
euclydes figueiredo was also severely reprimanded for defending 
cruzs criticisms in a separate article tinoco said 
in addition to scrapping the 29yearold secret service collor 
has irked a number of generals by opening up classified files of 
political opponents to the 196485 rightwing military regime 
figueiredo ended military rule by turning the presidency over to 
sarney a civilian but the military exerted great influence during 
the fiveyear sarney administration 
