<TEXT>
with memorial day on the horizon and 
floods in the foreground lake texoma businesses that spend 
millions to lure fishermen and boaters are worrying about swamped 
marinas and closed campsites 
intermittent rains fell over the region friday and showers are 
forecast for the next few days but some business owners hope they 
can recover in time for memorial day the first big holiday of the 
season 
you always think things wont get this bad said arnold 
perkins president of the lake texoma association weve had 
floods 10 to 15 feet above normal thats a bad flood were 
talking 24 feet above level now 
normal elevation at lake texoma on the red river at the texas 
line is 617 feet above sea level it crested monday at 64476 
feet dipped to 6414 friday but still sloshes windowhigh on 
mobile homes once 100 feet from its shore 
a restaurant disco and marina complex used by 5000 to 6000 
people a day during the summer was submerged and has been flooded 
for three weeks david hull who leases the property estimates 
damage at 2 million 
about 700 concession workers have been laid off because heavy 
rains in the region pushed the lake to its highest levels since it 
was built in 1944 
some campsites lodges and golf courses are open but word is 
out that lake texoma has suffered its worst flooding since 1957 
and that could be as big a blow to the tourism industry as the 
flooding itself perkins said 
the rains in oklahoma and texas filled lakes to their brims 
causing flooding in the two states and arkansas as water was 
released downstream on the arkansas and red rivers 
the army corps of engineers said its expects a greater volume of 
water to move safely through the red river flood control system 
than did in the disastrous floods of 1957 and 1927 texas had a 
dozen floodrelated deaths oklahoma one 
corps spokesman ed engelke said the 20 camping areas around lake 
eufaula in eastern oklahoma all have limited access because of high 
waters there he said rangers must check for damage before the 
sites are fully accessible 
downstream in arkansas where the arkansas river is receding 
from its crests at little rock and pine bluff the red river 
crested 8 feet above flood stage thursday at fulton and closed 
westbound lanes of interstate 30 
were looking at 80 square miles of flooding said jim 
barnes head of the us agricultural stabilization and 
conservation service in little river county it stretches for six 
miles 
oklahoma gov henry bellmon asked president bush on friday for 
federal disaster assistance for 36 of oklahomas 77 counties 
because of the floods 
in texas where severe flooding extended along the trinity river 
from north texas to the gulf coast the red has flooded 40 homes 
near texarkana where national guard troops were in their fourth 
day of reinforcing levees 
at lake grapevine near dallas some say it could take months for 
boat ramps to be reopened because of recent high waters 
summertime is like our christmas we only make it three months 
out of the year said terri berthelsen manager of the landing 
snack shop at the marina we pulled through last year on our 
savings this year we dont know what is going to happen 
on lake texoma caney creek resort owner virginia wornom said 
business slowed considerably in the last week and should stay 
through memorial day and beyond until people realize we havent 
floated off 
in the next two weeks all the marinas should be in condition 
to take care of the public perkins said but on friday about 
half were either under water or inaccessible 
perkins said water covered the roads leading to his marina in 
denison texas his restaurant once 5 feet deep in water reopened 
friday 
he and other proprietors say they cant begin to guess at the 
amount of the damage until the water recedes the corps of 
engineers has said it could be 45 to 60 days before the lake 
returns to a decent level 
perkins and other business owners have their eye on the holiday 
weekend traditionally a huge kickoff for a season that runs 
through labor day 
we were booked solid for memorial day but weve had a lot of 
cancellations said marion stone owner of soldier creek resort 
and marina people are not going to come to the lake 
james atnip superintendent of lake texoma state park said park 
officials are trying to be positive even though 270 of the 300 
campsites are closed and tree limbs and other debris are scattered 
across the lake 
theres not going to be a lake texoma this summer said mrs 
stone all the beaches are under water the water is murky the 
publicity has been harmful but we try not to mislead people 
</TEXT>
