the feud resumed thursday night when biden and bennett met on 
the macneillehrer newshour on the public broadcasting system 
bennett told biden sharply that you are trying to discredit 
our policy and we think this is just a bit disingenuous 
i dont like this rhetoric bill biden shot back i dont 
like these cheap shots about being disingenuous 
while bennett clung to the national drug strategys figure of 4 
million addicts biden pointed out that it referred to users of all 
kinds of drugs not just cocaine bennett retorted that most 
addicts abuse more than one drug both men conceded however that 
there was no way of getting a perfectly accurate count 
dr edgar adams of the national institute of drug abuse told 
reporters at bidens news conference that the senate report was a 
good attempt to look at what was a very complex problem 
he praised the report because it restates the fact that drug 
abuse is a very serious problem but he said there was a 95 
percent confidence level for the institutes smaller estimate and 
cautioned it might be hard to arrive at anything similar for the 
senate version 
the senate report put the number of hardcore addicts nationwide 
at 2159000 and said nearly one in every 100 americans is a weekly 
cocaine user 
some areas of the united states have extraordinarily high 
concentrations of addicts according to the report it said one 
out of every 40 individuals in new york state uses cocaine at least 
once a week 
the nations capital had the highest per capita rate 329 
hardcore users among every 1000 washington dc residents the 
report said 
the report was prepared under the supervision of mark ar 
kleiman of the kennedy school of government at harvard university 
biden said the results of the survey were tragic and urged a 
3 billion drugfighting plan ranging from research and development 
of new treatments to doubling law enforcement grants to 900 
million 
our consciences demand that we act our pocketbooks command 
that we do so and our safety demands that it be done immediately 
biden said 
the report said only one out of 10 hardcore addicts receives 
drug treatment and that most who are arrested quickly return to the 
streets 
the report estimated that new york state had the most hardcore 
addicts 434000 followed by california 325000 texas 144000 
illinois 142000 and florida 93000 
