<TEXT>
prosecutors seeking six new drug charges 
against mayor marion barry hope to show a pattern of drug use by 
the mayor sources familiar with the case say 
the new charges returned thursday include five counts of 
misdemeanor cocaine possession and a misdemeanor charge of 
conspiracy to possess cocaine they were added to an eightcount 
indictment including three felony perjury counts filed against 
the mayor in february 
the updated indictment alleges that barry possessed cocaine 
and crack with other coconspirators at more than 20 locations 
including private residences hotels government offices and 
business establishments and on boats 
the charges are intended to establish a pattern a practice of 
illegal activity that ranges over a period of years said a law 
enforcement source familiar with the case 
prosecutors have worried privately that r kenneth mundy 
barrys attorney might suggest in court that the mayor was 
unfairly lured into drug use on jan 18 the night of his arrest in 
an fbi sting operation sources said 
in order to battle that possible entrapment defense 
investigators have sought to portray barry as a regular drug user 
said the sources who spoke on condition of anonymity 
these new charges certainly suggest that he barry has done 
drugs on an awful lot of occasions over the past five or six 
years said one source was he an occasional or experimental 
user these charges suggest otherwise 
the new charges allege that barry conspired to possess cocaine 
and possessed the drug on numerous occasions between the fall of 
1984 and his arrest in january 
following the arrest barry spent seven weeks in rehabilitation 
facilities in florida and south carolina for treatment of what he 
said was alcohol and prescription drug abuse 
barry has pleaded innocent to the crimes with which he was 
charged in february herbert o reid sr the citys corporation 
counsel predicted the mayor will plead innocent to the new 
indictment as well 
one new charge says barry possessed cocaine on sept 7 1988 
two days after returning from a secret vacation at a health spa in 
the catskills mountains of new york state 
aides said later that the mayor was receiving dietary counseling 
and a variety of health treatments designed to help him lose weight 
and reduce his stress level 
in a statement us attorney jay b stephens spoke of the barry 
investigation as ongoing and a source familiar with the effort 
said the grand jury will continue hearing evidence 
barry refused to comment on his legal status but said his new 
troubles with the law will not affect his ability to govern 
im not looking for votes he said during an appearance at a 
senior citizens center im just being an elected official 
trying to do my job and trying to make sure the government goes to 
the people 
mundy barrys attorney complained that the charges should not 
have been lodged so close to the june 4 scheduled start of the 
mayors trial but he predicted that the trial would not be 
postponed 
barrys mayoral term ends this year and he has not yet said 
whether he will seek reelection to a fourth fouryear term 
however he has been touring the city and speaking to a wide array 
of community groups in campaignstyle appearances 
if convicted of a felony he would be barred from holding office 
or running for reelection once appeals were exhausted 
