nunn dga chairman of the panel 
president bushs defense budget for the fiscal year beginning 
oct 1 calls for 303 billion for the military a total that has 
come under attack in congress as too high 
the cbo director told the panel more than 43 billion could be 
saved over five to seven years by cutting the active duty forces 
and maintaining the current level of reserves 
according to the cbo 12 million people serve in the selected 
