vent along the volcanos east rift zone said hawaii county civil 
defense spokesman bruce butts 
surface activity was spotted at the 1800foot level during a 
overflight by scientists from the us geological surveys hawaiian 
volcano observatory butts said 
the activity was about five miles away from kalapana which has 
lost more than 60 houses to lava during the past six weeks he said 
although the outpouring of lava stopped earlier this week 
molten rock had continued to flow down the volcano through 
kalapana and into the ocean 
however no lava movement was seen in kalapana on thursday 
butts said 
kilaueas latest eruption began jane 3 1983 and since then 
lava flows have destroyed 139 houses causing an estimated 61 
million damage to private and public property 
