what was being negotiated and needed to plan for economic changes 
he told lawmakers on thursday that the east german negotiating 
team has gone into talks in a stooped posture to the west 
german delegation which wants to remove all the vestiges of the 
former socialist system 
the germanys are to merge their economies and social 
institutions on july 2 when the west german mark is to become the 
currency of east germany 
full unification is expected next year after the superpowers 
find a way to agree on the strategic role of a united germany 
krause said work on the final economic and social agreement 
between the germanys should be completed by sunday the parliaments 
of both nations then would consider the treaty 
in bonn west german chancellor helmut kohl said thursday that 
east germany must restructure its beleaguered economy before the 
two nations share the west german currency 
kohl also renewed his demand that east germany be prepared to 
start dismantling its 41yearold system of state ownership if 
economic union with west germany is going to be a success 
economists predict that many inefficient east german factories 
will close in the next year because they will not be able to 
compete in the free market and that between 500000 and 2 million 
east german workers will lose their jobs 
kohl and east german prime minister lothar de maiziere say a 
quick influx of western investment will create new jobs and raise 
east german living standards 
the two governments still have differences over the level of job 
and price guarantees to give east germans 
the talks are being held behind closed doors and many questions 
remain unanswered about how west germany would absorb and dismantle 
east germanys vast public sector and social welfare system 
the leftleaning social democrats the junior partner in de 
maizieres governing coalition are pressing the conservative de 
maiziere to push for more social guarantees for east germans used 
to cheap housing subsidized food and guaranteed jobs 
krause gave the 400member parliament an update on the status of 
talks between the countries and a grim economic picture of the east 
german economy 
he said east germany faces a yearend deficit of 120 billion 
east german marks 366 billion inflation has risen rapidly in 
recent months and only 32 percent of the nations industries are 
profitable 
