<TEXT>
a former deathrow inmate convicted in the 
mutilation slayings of his stepdaughter and her fiancee in 1982 was 
set free friday after prosecutors decided not to try him a second 
time 
dale johnston 56 who has maintained he is innocent emerged 
from the licking county jail promising to search for the real 
killer 
its a beautiful day johnston told reporters he met in his 
lawyers office in columbus 
he was freed secretly after the sheriffs department received a 
death threat against him said sheriff gerry billy 
three judges found johnston guilty in 1984 of aggravated murder 
in the slayings of his stepdaughter annette cooper johnston 18 
and her fiance todd schultz 19 both of logan in southeast ohio 
he was sentenced to death in the electric chair 
ms johnston and schultz were last seen oct 4 1982 in logan 
their torsos were discovered 10 days later in the hocking river 
other body parts were unearthed in a cornfield 
prosecutors alleged that johnston killed the two on his hocking 
county farm with a 22caliber handgun then dismembered their 
bodies prosecutors said jealousy was the motive for the killings 
and that johnston had a sexual relationship with his stepdaughter 
