the city council on friday urged police to 
bypass federal prosecutors in cases that could draw the new federal 
death penalty for drugconspiracy homicides 
the council approved 103 a nonbinding resolution urging police 
detectives in minnesotas largest city to present such cases to 
county or state prosecutors rather than the us attorney 
the action came one day after federal prosecutors in chicago 
announced the first use of the death penalty law enacted in 1988 
they said they would seek capital punishment for two men accused of 
killing a witness to protect a 50000aday drug ring 
the federal law allows capital punishment for murders committed 
to further drug conspiracies 
the minneapolis resolution won initial approval last week by a 
city council panel 
my personal opinion is that the death penalty serves no useful 
societal purpose council member joan campbell the resolutions 
chief sponsor said friday i dont think its the responsibility 
of a civilized society to kill people if they kill other people 
