northeast and gale warnings were in effect for lake erie lake 
ontario and the coasts of maine and new hampshire 
strong northwesterly winds prevailed across the lower great 
lakes region upper ohio valley and the middle and northern 
atlantic coast states strong northwesterly winds blew across north 
dakota and northwestern minnesota 
strong southerly winds prevailed from the southern plains to the 
middle mississippi valley 
strong and gusty winds also blew through the southwest winds at 
guadalupe pass texas gusted to 67 mph and wind advisories were 
posted through friday night for the deserts of southern california 
temperatures reached the 40s and upper 30s in parts of eastern 
wyoming and northeastern colorado on friday and into the 50s from 
the great lakes to new england 
temperatures were in the 80s across southern texas the florida 
peninsula and the desert southwest 
morning lows were in the 30s and 40s across much of the nation 
east of the mississippi river with readings in the 20s reported in 
wisconsin and upper michigan 
a number of cities reported record low temperatures for the 
date columbia mo had a low of 38 degrees a degree chillier 
than the 1952 record madison wis was 29 a degree lower than 
the 67 mark marquette mich was 23 25 in 1989 and paducah 
ky was 38 40 in 1969 
