<TEXT>
for french jews flourishing more than at any time 
in their history the desecration of tombstones in a southern town 
was a brutal reminder of frances long sordid history of 
antisemitism 
from the conviction of army officer alfred dreyfus nearly 100 
years ago to roundups of jews by french police during world war ii 
to the bombing of a paris synagogue in 1980 antisemitism remains 
a major fear among french jews 
antisemitism is a dormant volcano whose eruptions are never 
predictable wrote political analyst robert sole 
this weeks vandalism and mutilation of a recently buried corpse 
in carpentras came in an era of renewed jewish pride in france 
it also coincided with the steady rise of the extremeright 
national front a party that has rallied an estimated 15 percent of 
voters around an antiimmigrant racist platform that also targets 
jews 
its leader jeanmarie le pen prides himself on saying out 
loud what everybody is thinking to themselves he has joked about 
