peru hit hard by drought is calling on 
industrialized countries and the united nations to donate food to 
help it get through the next nine months a government spokesman 
said friday 
for the past year peru along with neighboring bolivia has been 
suffering the worst drought in the region this century the drought 
comes as peru copes with its worst economic crisis in 90 years 
the drought has led to strict water rationing in the capital 
lima and its port city of callao with a total population of 7 
million many outlying areas depend on water delivered by trucks 
limas mayor ricardo belmont has warned that the rimac river 
the citys main source of water may run dry by july 
perus electricity supply which comes mainly from hydroelectric 
complexes has also been cut by the drought 
only 14000 tons of food remain in the counrys storehouses 
said estuardo diaz head of perus national office of food support 
he said about 260000 tons of food were needed 
peru is seeking aid from the united states the european 
community and wheatrich argentina as well as the united nations 
diaz said 
agriculture ministry sources have said more than half perus 
annual crop of wheat rice and potatoes has been lost and next 
years crop is threatened 
the countrys andean mountain regions have been hardest hit 
many peasants are abandoning the countryside thousands of others 
have had to slaughter their cattle for lack of feed 
perus main wheat and riceproducing centers are mainly along 
the countrys arid pacific coast and are irrigated by rivers that 
flow out of the mountains which are running at far below normal 
levels 
no substantial relief is expected until the next rainy season 
in november 
rising guerrilla violence and the flood of peasants to the 
cities have driven down food production for the past decade last 
year peru imported 700 million worth of food 
now peru lacks foreign reserves to step up imports the annual 
inflation rate is topping 2000 percent and the government is all 
but bankrupt 
maoist shining path guerrillas have sought for years to cut the 
flow of food into lima hoping to spark an insurrection in the city 
