the wild wild west and in movies including butterfield 8 
and looking for love 
born charlotte gercke on feb 13 1937 in new york she was the 
daughter of astrology book author ruth oliver and george gercke a 
newsman who became a us information agency official in tokyo she 
lived there as a teenager 
she took up flying in 1964 and eventually began taking part in 
air races winning first place in the 1970 powder puff derby in 
addition to a private license she earned a commercial license and 
an instrument rating and also trained in a lear jet 
a week after her peyton place character was killed off she 
survived the crash of a piper cub near santa paula calif a friend 
was piloting 
in 1967 she flew a singleengine airplane across the atlantic by 
herself flying from new york to labrador greenland iceland 
scotland and finally denmark her hope of ending the trip in moscow 
was denied 
the flight was detailed in her 1983 book odyssey 
she did eventually get to moscow as a state department delegate 
to a film festival 
other television appearances included the invaders the 
virginian ben casey the rogues the outsiders 
man from uncle and the defenders 
she also had parts on episodes of bonanza the nurses 
dr kildare burkes law and the fugitive more 
recently she was in murder she wrote magnum pi and 
simon amp simon among others 
she directed episodes of mash and trapper john md 
miss olivers movie roles included greeneyed blonde the 
disorderly orderly your cheating heart a man called 
gannon change of mind and ginger in the morning 
a memorial service will be held at the american film institute 
in hollywood but the date has yet to be scheduled ms benson said 
