unrest in east germany 
tens of thousands of teachers textile workers and farmers 
staged brief protests and strikes on thursday to demand protection 
from the widespread unemployment expected as east germany moves to 
a free market economy 
klein said the strike organizers are to some extent exactly 
the forces who caused east germanys dire economic problems 
before last falls democratic upheaval ousted the communists from 
power 
