from 13990 million the week before 
the revival of optimism in the stock market by no means reflects 
a unanimously rosy view of the outlook 
indeed some economists on the street lately have lowered their 
estimates of growth for the spring and summer months at the same 
time that others are raising their projections 
inflation fears die hard especially in the bond market 
furthermore analysts remain mindful of how frequently and rapidly 
sentiment has shifted among investors recently 
the economy and inflation have given false signals in the 
past says the value line investment survey in its current 
appraisal of business prospects volatility is likely to remain 
the order of the day 
