<TEXT>
lawyers for three commodity traders facing 
federal fraud charges are keying their defense to the seeming 
bedlam of the futures markets 
they say the governments main witness an undercover fbi agent 
who observed and secretly taperecorded evidence of alleged 
wrongdoing at the chicago mercantile exchange was so befuddled by 
the frantic nature of commodity trading that he mistook the 
defendants legitimate actions for attempts to defraud customers 
its been referred to as organized chaos defense attorney 
alan blumenthal said of commodity trading during his opening 
statement thursday to the us district court jury 
it is within that confusion that you are going to question 
whether agent randall jannett had the opportunity to observe what 
he claims to have observed blumenthal said 
blumenthal is defending david zatz an independent trader of 
swiss franc futures who along with robert d mosky and danny l 
scheck faces multiple counts of mail or wire fraud and violating 
federal futurestrading rules 
mosky also is charged with racketeering conspiracy 
mosky worked as a floor broker filling customer orders from a 
number of brokerage firms as well as trading for his own account 
scheck was strictly an independent trader known as a local 
their trial before us district judge ann c williams is the 
first to result from an unprecedented fbi probe of trading fraud at 
the merc and the chicago board of trade the worlds two largest 
commodity futures markets 
prosecutors have portrayed the three as common criminals who 
conspired along with at least two other traders to divert to their 
own accounts profits that rightfully belonged to brokerage 
customers 
the government called its first witness thursday an 
investigator for the commodity futures trading commission who began 
the arduous task of educating the jury about commodity trading 
a swiss franc future is a contract to buy or sell a specified 
number of swiss francs at a future date at a price agreed upon in 
advance 
like other commodity futures swiss franc contracts are traded 
in a designated arena called a pit there traders stand shoulder 
to shoulder and strike deals through a rapidfire combination of 
hand signals and shouted bids and offers 
the governments case rests largely on conversations secretly 
recorded by jannett while he posed as a corrupt trader in the 
mercs swiss franc pit during the last 11 months of 1988 
prosecutors also plan to call as witnesses two other swiss franc 
traders william walsh and mark fuhrman who have pleaded guilty to 
fraud charges 
the defense lawyers discounted walsh and fuhrman as corrupt men 
who are seeking light sentences for their crimes 
and they portrayed jannett as determined to uncover trading 
fraud despite inadequate preparation for the frenzied confounding 
environment into which he was placed 
the fbi can send an agent into a trading pit but that wont 
make him a commodity trader said schecks lawyer harvey silets 
the government contends the fbi tapes reveal a variety of fraud 
schemes 
but silets and elliott samuels moskys lawyer said the tapes 
portray their clients proper attempts to verify trades they made 
with each other and jannett amid the hubbub of the trading pit 
prosecutors have stressed that the conversations jannett 
recorded were secretive which the government says indicates the 
traders were trying to conceal their actions 
but samuels said exchange and federal rules require traders to 
verbally confirm their trades immediately after they make them 
this tradechecking by nature has to be secret private 
oneonone samuels said 
thats what agent jannett recorded samuels said he 
recorded my clients compliance not violation of any rules 
the three men are the first suspects to be tried out of 47 
chicago futures traders and a clerk indicted last year as the 
result of the fbi sting operation 
sixteen of those indicted have pleaded guilty to reduced charges 
in return for their cooperation 
