63 percent comparablestore gain and a 159 percent rise overall 
in march k mart suffered a 11 percent drop in comparablestore 
sales 
calendar shifts such as easter falling on a different date 
from one year to another can affect retail sales inflating one 
months figure and detracting from another the industry tends to 
consider march and april together in assessing how well stores did 
kurt barnard a retailing consultant said the stores that have 
done the best cater to consumers seeking higherquality merchandise 
at a moderate price in a very attractive and exciting ambiance 
he cited limited and gap as examples of such retailers 
analysts said consumers burdened by high installment debt 
continue to be conservative and wary about more expensive purchases 
like large appliances retailers dependent on such items have had 
lackluster sales gains compared with the improvement by apparel 
stores 
analysts predict the trend will continue until later this year 
several of the nations biggest retailers including sears 
roebuck amp co walmart stores inc jc penney co inc and 
woolworth corp reported their april results a week ago and they 
also reflected the split between sales of apparel and more 
expensive items 
the figures released thursday differ from the federal 
governments monthly retail sales report besides stores the 
governments figures include sales at a range of establishments 
from auto dealerships and supermarkets to restaurants and movie 
theaters 
