this means the battle over chinas trade status with the united 
states a crucial part of their relationship could be prolonged 
china and its allies on this issue in the american business 
community have begun readying for the fray only the latest round 
in washingtons debate over whether sanctions help or hurt the 
cause of democracy in china 
the united states imposed limited economic sanctions last year 
but bush has eased several such as a ban on hightech exports 
signaling how seriously china takes the threat to mfn in the 
past two weeks it lifted martial law in the tibetan city of lhasa 
and announced the release of 211 prodemocracy protesters both 
moves were widely seen as an effort to counter criticism of its 
human rights record 
it also disclosed that authorities allowed 238000 people go 
abroad on private business last year which it said was up 11 
percent from the previous year us law bars giving mfn status to 
any country that denies residents freedom of emigration 
